<HEADLINE>
TROJANS WELCOME PALMER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC opens spring football practice Thursday, and
all eyes will be on sophomore quarterback Carson Palmer, who is
returning after missing nine games with a broken collarbone.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer's return could be one reason the Trojans are opening
practice earlier than ever, although USC coach Paul Hackett said he
also started sooner because he has so many new assistant coaches
who need to become familiar with the personnel.
</P>
<P>
   But the big news of spring figures to be how quickly Palmer can
come back from his injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's been throwing on his own and feels good,'' Hackett said.
``I think there will still be a fatigue factor. I anticipate a
reduction in his reps the first two days and then using him for
full reps on our third practice, which will be March 23rd.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Position changes:Several players have been moved on defense.
Starting free safety Ife Ohalete has moved to strong safety.
Linebacker Sultan Abdul-Malik has returned to defensive end, and
defensive end Kori Dickerson is playing strongside linebacker, the
position formerly occupied by Abdul-Malik.
</P>
<P>
   __ Sitting out spring: Linebacker Markus Steele, who had
shoulder surgery in December, will not participate in contact
drills during spring practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is no way we'll put him in a contact situation,''
Hackett said. ``There's a lot of things he can do without putting
on pads.''
</P>
<P>
   Without Steele, the outside-linebacker spot will be occupied by
Daryl Knight, Henry Wallace and JC transfer John Cousins.
</P>
<P>
   Also missing spring practice are tailback Petros Papadakis, who
is recovering from a broken foot, and defensive back Antuan
Simmons, who had back surgery in November.
</P>
<P>
   __ Michels returns: Former USC offensive lineman John Michels,
who played for the Super Bowl champion Green Bay Packers and on the
1996 Rose Bowl championship team, has been hired as a graduate
assistant.
</P>
<P>
   __ True freshman to play: Hackett mentioned that offensive
lineman Joe McGuire, tight end Alex Holmes and strong safety Matt
Grootegoed would all play next season.
</P>
<P>
   The most intriguing possibility is that Grootegoed could be used
in some situations as a tailback.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had an argument this morning about whether we could do
that,'' Grootegoed said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Spring dates: The Trojans will practice March 9, 10, 23, 24,
25, 28, 30, 31, April 4, 6, 7, 8, 11, 13 and 15.
</P>
<P>
   USC will hold scrimmages on March 31 and April 8, with another
to be determined. All practices are open to the public.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
