<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKW-UTA-SW-TEXAS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOUTHWEST TEXAS STATE'S INSIDE GAME PUSHES UT-ARLINGTON OUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TRACEY MYERS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN MARCOS _ UT-Arlington women's basketball team was
controlling the inside against Southwest Texas State, getting the
defensive rebounds and the points.
</P>
<P>
   But when the Mavericks got away from that plan, the Bobcats,
specifically senior Shawn Manning, made them pay.
</P>
<P>
   Manning finished with a game-high 23 points as the Bobcats
knocked off UTA, 70-54, in a first-round game of the Southland
Conference tournament at Strahan Coliseum last night.
</P>
<P>
   UTA (13-15) led 27-26 at halftime. But after a short
conversation at the half _ coach Suzanne Fox clocked it at a minute
and a half _ the Bobcats (18-10) regrouped and dominated the paint
to win their 10th consecutive game.
</P>
<P>
   SWT will play Northwestern State at 8 p.m. Friday in Shreveport,
La.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought we came out and fought hard, but I thought, in the
second half, they got the ball to the high post \RManning\S ,'' UTA
coach Mike Dean said. ``The first 10 or 15 minutes \Rof the second
half\S, they just threw it in there whenever they wanted. We needed
to do a better job of denying that.''
</P>
<P>
   Jalila Darez led the Mavs with 18 points and 11 rebounds. Renee
Wharekura, sidelined most of the first half because of a sprained
right ankle, finished with 13. Tasha Campbell scored 10.
</P>
<P>
   Manning, a 6-foot-1 forward, had her way inside in the second
half. The Bobcats, after being outrebounded 23-15 in the first
half, took 22 to UTA's 12 in the second.
</P>
<P>
   ``They were beating us on the boards and, really, that's our
stronghold.'' Manning said. ``So, it got us fired up to go out and
make sure we blocked out and did what we had to do to get them off
the boards.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
