display in New York in a showing similar to one in Chicago earlier
this year. The cows are then sponsored by corporations, with prices
of $7,500 to $350,000, said Daniel Blume, vice president of
Connecticut-based Cow Parade Holding Corp. After expenses, Cow
Parade Holding earns profits from the sponsorships. When the cows
are later auctioned, local charities will receive up to 80 percent
of the proceeds. (Bill Speer/Sarasota Herald Tribune)
