Pi-Ro's director, said it was impossible to compete with the flood
of cheap Korean and Chinese syringes in recent years, and Brazilian
officials were offering a package of tax-breaks and subsidized
loans to relocate to Brazil. ``I'm an Argentine and I would like to
believe in my county's future,'' he said, ``but if there is no
national policy to save us and we can't compete, its time to
move.'' (Horacio Paone/The New York Times)
