are more frustrating than a car that won't start because of a weak
battery. StartMeUp is an emergency battery charger that weighs only
six ounces and easily fits in a glove compartment where it stays
usable for three years. If you attempt to start your car and get
only the clicking noise associated with a drained battery, you plug
StartMeUp into the cigarette lighter receptacle. After five minutes
of charging, the car will start, according to Future Labs, the
Philadelphia company that developed StartMeUp. (Cox News Service)
