Jackie Cottrill's kitchen may look like it's straight out of a
decorating magazine, but, being an avid cook, she insists it's used
every day. She designed the kitchen herself, at a cost of $150,000.
It features a mixture of surface materials and hidden appliances,
but the secret is in her own design. ``A kitchen is a necessity,
but I didn't want mine to look like one,'' says Cottrill, with her
cat Tobias. ``I wanted it to look like a room with nice
furniture.'' (Louie Favorite/The Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
