Whether his actions will be sufficient to repair Argentina's
economy remains a big question, but even his critics say they are
surprised by the vigorous pace of reform from the president, who
dared to suggest that he was a boring fellow in a signature
television advertisement during his campaign. By Clifford Krauss.
