<HEADER>
A0538 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE09     03-08 0805
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    WRESTLING GRAPEVINE
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before they have even gotten off the ground, the new Nitro Girls
have already lost a member. Skye, who is also Miss Hancock, will be
leaving the Nitro Girls to work more with her new character that
seems to be taking off. Of course, her character and all women's
characters may be wiped from the WCW slate by summer.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of women troubles, the red-hot rumor of the week is
that the WWF's favorite busty EMT, Barbara Bush, will get her
walking papers soon because of her out-of-the-ring relationship
with Bob Holly.
</P>
<P>
   While Bush may be on the way out, WWF officials are trying to
find a place for Mideon. Mideon's acting job as the fake Mankind
last month opened their eyes to his talent and could result in the
new gimmick soon.
</P>
<P>
   WCW's woes were increased when the official buy rate for the
most recent pay-per-view were announced. ``Superbrawl'' pulled in
about 250,000 buyers _ one of the least watched pay-per-views in
WCW history.
</P>
<P>
   Troubles for the struggling organization continued when Terry
Taylor, the man who has run the booking committee and wrote the
television scripts for the past two months, stepped down from his
role on the booking committee. He is expected to spend more time
concentrating on the road agent aspects of his job. Taylor has been
the bridge from the end of the Vince Russo reign and the fallout of
the Kevin Sullivan reign.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Madden stated on ``WCW Live'' recently that the Macho Man
Randy Savage's valet and girlfriend, Gorgeous George, has been busy
working strip clubs across the country during her time away from
WCW. Savage's contract with WCW is to expire soon, as well as his
career, as he doesn't seem to have a role in the WWF and is too
expensive for ECW. So fans may not see George in the ring, but I'm
sure they'd settle for the strip club near them.
</P>
<P>
   Although his wife, Luna, was fired, Gangrel remains in the WWF,
although any shot at the top has been put on the back burner.
</P>
<P>
   Despite serious injuries, Bret Hart and Kevin Nash will be with
WCW during their European swing this week. Neither will wrestle
though.
</P>
<P>
   An update on ECW's ``Hardcore Revolution'' video game: Acclaim
Entertainment announced that the game had climbed the charts in
just two days to become the No. 2-selling video game on the
PlayStation and No. 6 on Nintendo 64. ``We are very pleased with
the initial response to ECW: Hardcore Revolution,'' said Brad
Loucks, vice president of Acclaim sales. ``We have already sold
over 600,000 units, and have received reorders from virtually every
major retailer.''
</P>
<P>
   Many different Internet reports are that the WCW contacted
Mexican wrestlers El Dandy and Silver King about working some
matches for the company. Many wrestlers believe that they were
called only because of Sonny Onoo's racial discrimination lawsuit
against WCW.
</P>
<P>
   Another hot rumor spreading across the Internet is that Hulk
Hogan will have the WCW world title around his waist before April.
That would build to a Hogan vs. Goldberg matchup in mid-April.
Something will happen soon because WCW is staring at a Sid
Vicious-Jeff Jarrett main event at their ``Uncensored''
pay-per-view, which promises to be one of the worst pay-per-view
main events ever. Despite their age, Hogan, Ric Flair and Terry
Funk seem to draw the most interest in their story lines from the
fans.
</P>
<P>
   One of those young wrestlers who can't stay healthy is Buff
Bagwell. With his WCW contract set to expire March 31, he has
reportedly asked for a seven-figure renewal, and if he doesn't get
it, he will definitely quit WCW. One problem to that scenerio:
Where is he going to go to get that kind of money? With the recent
signings of Chris Benoit, Perry Saturn, Dean Malenko and Eddy
Guerrero, the WWF has stocked its roster with plenty of young
talent and Bagwell's gimmick is just like The Rock's, with less
appeal. ECW is too rough for Bagwell, who's pretty boy image
wouldn't work in the rough and tumble ECW, plus they don't have the
kind of money he wants. So, it looks like Bagwell will stay and
won't be getting a pay raise. While having trouble finding a
position in the WWF, Vic Grimes has found his niche while on loan
to the ECW. Grimes has been involved in some nasty matches, even by
ECW standards, and seems to be more than willing to crash through
the wall or table or chair to get the job done. His recent
Exploding Death Match with Balls Mahoney could go down in ECW
infamy.
</P>
<P>
   The television ratings war isn't much of a battle anymore. The
last Monday in Feb. saw Raw gain a 6.5 rating compared to Nitro's
2.6. In the head-to-head hour it was Raw with a 6.5 to 2.2
advantage.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
