<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BOURQUE-CAREER (Boston) _ The joke was that Ray Bourque
would be the only Bruin to have his jersey retired while he was
still wearing it. Twenty-one years, 1,518 games, nearly 50,000
minutes. More than twice as many as Bobby Orr, the legend he
conceded he could never be. By John Powers. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
