book about the civil rights leader _ ``I May Not Get There With
You: The True Martin Luther King Jr.'' _ that suggests that King
had a number of flaws that would have tarnished his image had he
lived. Still, Dyson, a Baptist minister, believes that King's
legacy is greater because he was flawed and not reluctant to admit
his mistakes to followers. By JEFF GUINN. Story will move in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
