   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   AIRPORT-EXPANSION (Los Angeles) _ Nationwide the battle lines
are drawn over airports' need to expand vs. their neighbors' rights
to peace, quiet and clean air. By Matthew Brelis. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   HMO-PEROT (Undated) _ Ross Perot says he and Charlie Baker are
building a computer system that will be the template for the
national HMO of the future. His vision could only be accomplished
in Boston, he says, because it's ``full of genius doctors.'' By Liz
Kowalczyk. 1220 words.
</P>
<P>
   ONJOBS-COLUMN (Undated) -- With so many US firms now involved in
international business deals, companies are finding that
familiarity with the host country's customs is critical. By Diane
E. Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ It doesn't take much to move tech
stocks these days. Analyst price targets are sending tech stocks to
the moon. By Steven Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (Undated) _ A young couple, both 35, wonder if
their retirement savings are adequate. By Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
