<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    'DIGITAL DIVIDE' POSES CHALLENGE TO FIRST 'E-LECTION'
 &HT;    Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
 &HT;    By ANDREW J. GLASS
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The nation's first Internet election, hailed by its
backers as a historic breakthrough, risks running afoul of federal
voting rights laws.
</P>
<P>
   ``After the process ends Saturday, there'll be a trial on the
