 For Release THURSDAY AMs, March 9, 2000  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta
 &LR; at the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of
graphics or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COLOMBIA-AID (Washington) _ Despite a long list of concerns over
the Clinton administration's $1.3 billion emergency package to
fight drugs in Colombia, a House committee will consider a bill
offering even more money _ a $427 million increase. By John
Donnelly. 1000 words. (i and w coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-FUTURE (Washington) _ The instant analysis of the
looming fall matchup between Vice President Al Gore and Texas
Governor George W. Bush is that it all sounds so familiar. The son
of the former president takes on the vice president who helped
retire his father. Call it 1992 redux: the grudge match. By Michael
Kranish. 1500 words.
</P>
