<DOCNO> NYT20000308.0314 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-08 19:04 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0929 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r a BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     03-08 0806
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 Copyright 2000 Chronicle Publishing Company 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NOTE: THERE WILL BE NO PERSONALS MOVED THURSDAY MARCH 9 for &LR; 
 &UR; MARCH 10. WILL RESUME SUNDAY FOR MONDAY.  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ONE MAN'S TALE OF THE GREELY EXPEDITION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   rt,10p10 Historian  &UR; Leonard Guttridge &LR; 's new book, ``Ghosts of
Cape Sabine'' (Putnam's; $27.95), tells the story of 25 American
soldiers who set forth in July 1881 to establish a scientific base
