execution and, as the book reveals, cannibalism.
</P>
<P>
   One of the central characters in the tale is  &UR; Frederick &LR; 
 &UR; Kislingbury &LR; , who began the expedition as second in command.
 &UR; Linda Kislingbury Cain &LR; , great-granddaughter of Kislingbury, lives
in Novato and owns many papers relating to the expedition,
including his diary and letters from him to her grandfather,
 &UR; Douglass Kislingbury &LR; . The letters reveal him to be a loving
father.
</P>
<P>
   On August 8, 1881, for example, the lieutenant wrote to his
