   &UR; THE `SUPER TUESDAY' SHAKEDOWN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   After a dramatic sweep of Democratic primaries by Vice President
Al Gore and a series of one-sided victories by Governor George W.
Bush in the biggest Republican primaries Tuesday, the two
candidates lost no time Wednesday in turning their attentions
toward the general election in November. ``It's going to be a very
tough, no-holds-barred campaign,'' predicted American University
history professor Allan Lichtman, ``because both Bush and Gore have
shown they'll do whatever it takes to win.'' &QL;
</P>
