<HEADER>
A1000 &Cx1f; taf-z
u f BC-ABC-NEWS-EXECS-NYT &LR;      03-08 0322
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ABC-NEWS-EXECS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THREE AT ABC GET NEW POSITIONS IN REVAMPING OF NEWS DIVISION 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 By BILL CARTER   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ ABC realigned the management of its news division
Wednesday by giving three executives new duties under the
division's president, David Westin.
</P>
<P>
   One change will be a new executive producer of the network's
evening newscast, anchored by Peter Jennings. Westin also said he
was considering a further shrinking of the number of news magazine
programs that ABC News will produce for prime time.
</P>
<P>
   ABC began the current television season with four weekly
editions of its news magazine ``20/20.'' It is now down to three,
and the program's ratings have been slipping. ``It is entirely
possible that we'll go down to two,'' Westin said.
</P>
<P>
   Westin said the changes were intended to prepare ABC News for
what he called the ``radical changes'' like digital technology that
face the broadcast industry.
</P>
<P>
   To rethink ABC strategy, Westin named Paul Friedman, who has
been the executive producer of the evening newscast, ``World News
Tonight,'' to a new management position, executive vice president
and managing editor for news coverage. Westin said Friedman would
be in charge of overseeing the process of moving ABC News ``into
the new technological world.''
</P>
<P>
   Friedman will also help select a new executive producer for the
newscast along with Westin and Jennings, Westin said.
</P>
<P>
   Westin named Phyllis McGrady, one the most experienced
executives at ABC, to a new post supervising all the division prime
time programs as well as its morning show ``Good Morning America.''
</P>
<P>
   The third executive elevated to new duties is Bob Murphy, who
was formerly in charge of hard news for the network. Westin named
Murphy senior vice president for multimedia. He will supervise all
aspects of the news division's expansion into digital and wireless
technologies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-08-00 2010EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
