officers and other witnesses. And in Queens, juries are deadlocking
in an increasing number of cases, a sign, prosecutors fear, that
jurors are questioning the veracity of police testimony as police
misconduct scandals continue to dominate city headlines. A juror
examined his handbook and summons card. (Ruby Washington/The New
