progenitor of the present. The persistent suggestion of his fiction
is this: From there, we got here. But in his new novel, ``City of
God,'' his 10th, he has taken a reverse tack. ``In this book, it
seems I've finally caught up to the present,'' Doctorow said his
latest novel. ``I've been very slow about it, but I finally made
it.'' (Ruth Fremson/The New York Times) LITE
