   (NYT2) AUSTIN, Texas -- March 8, 2000 -- BUSH-2 -- Gov. George
W. Bush of Texas marks his ballot as he voted absentee for the
Texas primary, Wednesday. The presidential primary in Texas will be
held on March 14. Bush declared a ``national victory'' in
Republican primaries Tuesday and immediately set his sights on
likely Democratic nominee Al Gore as a symbol of the the status quo
in Washington. (Stephen Crowley/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) AUSTIN, Texas -- March 8, 2000 -- BUSH-1-- Gov. George
Bush of Texas and his wife Laura on the grounds of the governor's
mansion Wednesday. Bush declared a ``national victory'' in
Republican primaries Tuesday and immediately set his sights on
likely Democratic nominee Al Gore as a symbol of the the status quo
in Washington. (Stephen Crowley/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
