<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS WAIT FOR DECISION FROM MITCHELL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The Cowboys are continuing the waiting game with
free-agent quarterback Scott Mitchell, who is mulling offers from
Dallas and Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys have not talked to Mitchell since making him a
contract offer Monday to replace Jason Garrett as Troy Aikman's
primary backup. Mitchell, who would likely have a better chance of
playing next season as a backup in Cincinnati, said he wanted some
time to think about his decision.
</P>
<P>
   The Bengals have not spoken to Mitchell in a couple of days,
either. But they believe the quarterback is leaning their way
because his agent asked them to send a contract to Mitchell on
Tuesday. However, a signed contract has not yet been sent back to
Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys signed former Arena League quarterback Charles
Puleri to a one-year deal yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   And free-agent tight end Jackie Harris, who played 12 games for
Tennessee last season, was at the Cowboys' training complex
yesterday; the Cowboys are considering signing him to back up David
LaFleur.
</P>
</TEXT>
